Runtime plugins have two names, the name in the config file and the name in the plugin class. For example, the current Biothings plugin in the plugin store has this config:
```json
{
  "name": "Biothings",
  // ...other stuff
}
```
And this plugin class name:
```js
export default class extends Plugin {
  name = 'MyGeneAdapter'

  install(pluginManager: PluginManager) {
    // stuff
  }
}
```

When you see this plugin in the plugin store, it looks like this:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25592344/121971854-f9ee3c80-cd36-11eb-986d-c718d89104e6.png)
But when you install it, it uses the plugin class name instead:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25592344/121971904-18543800-cd37-11eb-8559-f285ac7eb909.png)

The name inconsistencies cause a few problems:

- The plugin still shows available to install even when it's already installed
- It shows a lock icon and doesn't allow removing the plugin, even if it's a session plugin
- In admin mode, it doesn't show a lock icon, but when you try to remove the plugin it doesn't actually get removed

There probably needs to be a way to deduplicate the two names or ensure they are the same.

