Fixes #1298 

The reason bug #1289 showed up in Travis builds was because if you run `yarn build` on just jbrowse-web, it builds from the uncompiled plugins. But if you run `yarn build` on the whole repo (like Travis does) it builds the plugins first and then builds jbrowse-web from the compiled plugins. The bug was in the plugin compilation, so it showed up in the Travis build.

I tracked the bug down to `babel-plugin-transform-async-to-promises`, which is used in TSDX's rollup config. Under some circumstances, the code was being compiled down to something like this:

```js
class A {
  constructor() {
    const _this = this
    super()
    // stuff that uses `_this`
  }
}
```

Since `this` was being accessed before `super()`, it failed. It looks like `babel-plugin-transform-async-to-promises` is known to be a bit buggy, though, since TSDX removed it in https://github.com/formium/tsdx/commit/2aefc3d776d7d3e0d9e645c8e5263c6623e987c9. Luckily, the latest version of TSDX contains this fix, so we can update to that.

Upgrading TSDX brings Jest 25 into our dependencies, which `react-scripts` doesn't like, so we add Jest 24 as a devDependency of jbrowse-web (this is a special case of having a devDependency not in the root `package.json`).

Upgrading TSDX also broke parsing of [optional chaining](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Operators/Optional_chaining), and after a bunch of digging I found out that it was because of the root `.browserslistrc` (which was presumably getting referenced by `@babel/preset-env` somewhere). I removed the file to allow it to use the defaults, which fixed optional chaining parsing. I don't think `.browserslistrc` was being relied on by any other code since all the places we call `@babel/preset-env` we specify `target`, which overrides browserslist, and jbrowse-web and jbrowse-desktop override browserslist in their `package.json`s.

Also removes a couple of now-unused `tsdx.config.js` files as well as `rollup-plugin-scss` (SCSS was removed in #1270).

